<br>
We are recommending changes to these 2 rules because they were originally written as a compromise with CIW.  CIW not only does not exist on The Rathe, but the hostile relations between the guilds does not as well.<br>
<br>
Both rules are entirely out of date and no longer accurately reflect the current situation of The Rathe.  (Espically the Epic guild rules, which contain a broken link, on top of not being inforced for the previous 4 months.)<br>
<br>
We do not agree with the arguement that guilds will need to bail out these smaller guilds.  We strongly believe that your plane date is yours and yours alone and do not support a system of any type that encourages bail outs of other guilds in the planes.  <br>
<br>
If a guild gets wiped out, we believe that it is THAT guild's responsiblity to regain the zone, ask their friends, or wait until the next raid.  If a 30 person guild gets wiped out, then they will have learned something the hard way.  It is not our place to protect them.<br>
<br>
We have always supported lowering the minimum number, and originally suggested the 30 minimum rule (with max 6 invites).<br>
<br>
FK votes YES on both proposals (duh).<br>
<br>
