<br>
SoT has 74 active members.  Yes, we keep close watch on this, in case you want to know.<br>
<br>
We usually have at least 30 at a Fear Raid.<br>
<br>
That's about half, and most are level 60.<br>
<br>
If a guild, who is JUST reaching Planar Levels, and has only 30, let's say they can field 15.  How do they expect to do it?<br>
<br>
Don't say &quot;ask another guild&quot;, cause you can only have 6 from any other entity, else they'll be breaking that 'rule'.<br>
<br>
IF they have their 15, and 30 from various other guilds, then how it is *their* Raid?<br>
<br>
If they go in with their 15, and get wiped out, and ask another guild to CR them, and then &quot;help&quot; them do Fear, this would also not be *their* Raid.<br>
<br>
This type of abuse is why the 40 to post was put into place, and has been working fine.<br>
<br>
This is my opinion only, not that of SoT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uemilsinclair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emil Sinclair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blood of the Spider</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/01 2:06:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposed: Lowering minimum number for calendar to 30</span><hr size=1> I'm inclined to throw a 'no' to this proposal.<br>
<br>
On the surface, it looks nice, liberal, lax, etc.. less admin, less governing.<br>
<br>
But - when you apply it to a real situation, here's what you get (at least in my eyes):<br>
<br>
If the new rule was to allow a guild with 30 plansable to register to got to fear, that guild would (i'd imagine) need 95-100% attendance to enter fear. This is quite demanding, when you think about it. <br>
<br>
So 1 of 2 things would most likely occur: Firstly, the guild would get 100% attendance, and clear fear - hooray; or secondly the guild would get 75% or less attendance (pretty typical in my experience, and seems to be the case with other guilds) and either a) find the need to invite en masse or b) get blown out, and require CR.<br>
<br>
The stipulation for requiring 40 plansable takes into consideration the fact that its quite rare to have 100% guild attendance for any given raid, thus it gives that guild some leeway when the scheduled raid comes up.<br>
<br>
I don't see it too terribly difficult to either recruit 10 more people (lotta people on the server) or to form an alliance. <br>
<br>
It's not aboot excluding people from places, as much as trying to ensure that when an entity registers a day in fear/hate/sky - they will have a decent time there, while also keeping the entities participating in the registered raids to a decent minimum, thus allowing for multiple schedulings per month, as seems to be the case since the split.<br>
<br>
Of course, if you have more than 40 plansables, you can enter fear with 6 - for all anyone cares.. its just about setting a reasonable requirement to be allowed to post. Again, the requirement is set up to ensure the guild/alliance can handle it (taking into consideration typical attendance) and trimming down registering entities to allow for more than 1 appointment per month.<br>
<br>
If this proposal were to pass, i would strongly ask for a clause that states that if a &lt; 30 member guild has to seek CR, they need to be restricted from registering for 30 days or so. CR is a pain for those directly involved, as well as those coming to aid...would be a hassle if it happened more often than not.  <p><table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#000000" bordercolorlight="#808080" bordercolordark="#000000">
